.TH LU\-DEPS 1 "2026-04-27" "logicutils 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lu\-deps \- dependency graph analysis and conversion
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lu\-deps
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fIINPUT\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B lu\-deps
reads a dependency graph from a variety of source formats, performs
analysis (transitive closure, reverse lookup, topological sort), and
emits the result in a chosen target format. The internal graph is a
directed multi\-edge map from targets to dependencies.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-from= FORMAT
Input format: \fImakefile\fR, \fIgcc\fR (output of
.BR "gcc \-M" ),
\fIlu\-rules\fR (a rule file as understood by
.BR lu\-rule (1)),
or \fItsv\fR.
.TP
.BI \-\-to= FORMAT
Output format: \fItsv\fR (default), \fIcsv\fR, \fIdot\fR, \fIjson\fR,
\fItoml\fR, \fItaskfile\fR (the format consumed by
.BR lu\-par (1)).
.TP
.B \-\-transitive
Expand each node\(cqs dependency list to include all transitive
predecessors.
.TP
.BI \-\-reverse \  TARGET
Print every node that transitively depends on \fITARGET\fR.
.TP
.B \-\-topo
Print nodes in topological order. Cycles cause an error.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success, 1 if a cycle is detected when one is forbidden, 2 on
error.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Convert
.B "gcc \-M"
output to a
.BR lu\-par (1)
task file:
.PP
.RS
.nf
gcc \-M \-MM main.c | lu\-deps \-\-from=gcc \-\-to=taskfile > tasks.tsv
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lu\-par (1),
.BR lu\-rule (1)
.SH AUTHOR
NEWSNIPER.
